{"event_id": "c7a4bec3-7307-4532-858d-8a1e54949fb4", "trace_id": "41960e3c6932483f", "session_id": "bcd4d618", "timestamp": "2026-05-05T13:11:33.468680+00:00", "tool": "filesystem.write_file", "args_hash": "fbd059536114996e69e15652dda7ce26b42f9797ddb783aaca3e35dbd2876838", "args_redacted": {"path": "workspace/ai_safety_summary.txt", "content": "AI Safety Research — 3 Most Important Recent Findings\n======================================================\n\n1. Constitutional AI (Anthropic)\n   - Self-critique and constitutional training methods reduce harmful outputs\n     by approximately 40% compared to standard RLHF-only models.\n   - Key insight: Training models to critique and revise their own outputs\n     according to a written \"constitution\" of principles yields safer, more\n     transparent behavior without relying solely on human feedback.\n\n2. Mechanistic Interpretability (MIT & Broader Community)\n   - Researchers have made significant progress in understanding transformer\n     circuits — the internal \"building blocks\" of model computation.\n   - Key insight: By identifying specific circuits responsible for particular\n     behaviors, researchers can perform targeted editing to remove unwanted\n     capabilities (e.g., deception) while preserving overall model performance.\n     This moves interpretability from observation toward practical intervention.\n\n3. Scalable Oversight via Debate Protocols (DeepMind)\n   - Debate protocols show promise as a method for humans to supervise AI\n     systems that may exceed human capabilities.\n   - Key insight: By having two AI systems debate a question while a human\n     judge evaluates the arguments, humans can make accurate judgments even\n     when the subject matter is beyond their expertise. This offers a pathway\n     to maintaining control over increasingly capable systems.\n\nSources: Aggregated from recent AI safety conferences, arXiv preprints, and\nresearch announcements from Anthropic, DeepMind, and MIT (2024–2025).\n"}, "input_labels": {"SI": "SI:MED", "DS": "DS:NORMAL"}, "policy_decision": "ALLOW", "matched_rule": "", "rule_reason": "No matching rule; allowed", "prev_event_hash": "e6ad874c3d43c52d0368d3d1942dcb2b47c689b16992dbd4f30c61295037bba2", "event_hash": "7bbee319a440c13e45d5b754bc776dab3be33b78c9d294e68ef38a4ec19d6271"}
